1. Executive Summary

This document defines the complete product requirements for the Tinder Reviews Sentiment Analysis Platform — an end-to-end NLP mini-project that collects, processes, and visualises user sentiment from app store reviews of Tinder and competing dating applications.

The platform goes beyond simple positive/negative classification. It incorporates aspect-based sentiment analysis, trend detection over time, fake review filtering, rating-text mismatch flagging, and a React-based interactive dashboard — making it a comprehensive, portfolio-ready project that demonstrates real-world NLP engineering skills.

The system is designed to be modular, extensible, and academically sound, with a clearly documented NLP pipeline that can be presented during project vivas.

2. Project Overview

2.1 Problem Statement
App store reviews are one of the richest, most unfiltered sources of user feedback available for consumer applications. However, Tinder and similar dating apps accumulate thousands of reviews monthly, making manual analysis impractical. There is a need for an automated, intelligent pipeline that can:
•Classify sentiment at scale (positive, negative)
•Identify which specific aspects of the app are causing satisfaction or dissatisfaction
•Track how sentiment evolves over time (correlated with app updates or features)
•Detect anomalies such as spam reviews or mismatched star ratings
•Present insights in a clear, interactive visual dashboard

2.2 Goals & Objectives
•Build a complete, reproducible NLP pipeline from data collection to visualisation
•Achieve >80% accuracy on sentiment classification using BERT or equivalent
•Provide aspect-level sentiment breakdown across 5+ product dimensions
•Enable comparative analysis across Tinder, Bumble, and Hinge
•Deliver a working web dashboard with real-time review upload support
•Produce a clean, well-documented codebase suitable for GitHub portfolio

