4.2 Feature Specifications
F-01 — Data Collection
The system shall scrape Google Play Store reviews for Tinder, Bumble, and Hinge using the google-play-scraper Python library. It shall collect a minimum of 5,000 reviews per application, including review text, star rating, date, and review thumbs-up count. Data shall be persisted as CSV files for reproducibility.

F-02 — Text Preprocessing Pipeline
The pipeline shall apply the following transformations in order:
•Lowercase normalisation
•URL and HTML tag removal
•Emoji removal or replacement with text equivalents
•Punctuation and special character stripping
•Stopword removal (NLTK English corpus)
•Lemmatisation using spaCy en_core_web_sm
•Short review filtering (< 5 tokens after preprocessing)

F-03 — Sentiment Classification (2-class)
The system shall support sentiment classification approaches, selectable via configuration:
•Basic: Multinomial Naive Bayes / Logistic Regression with TF-IDF features
•Mid-tier: VADER (rule-based) and TextBlob (pattern-based)
•Advanced: Fine-tuned BERT (bert-base-uncased via HuggingFace Transformers)
Output labels: Positive, Negative with confidence scores. The system shall report accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score on a held-out test set.

F-04 — Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis
The system shall identify sentiment for the following aspects within each review:
Aspect	Keywords / Signals	Example Trigger Phrase
UI / UX	interface, design, layout, navigation, simple, confusing	"The new UI is clean and easy to use"
Pricing	price, subscription, premium, gold, expensive, free, cost, refund	"Gold subscription is way too expensive"
Matches / Algorithm	match, like, algorithm, profile, swipe, boost	"The matching algorithm shows irrelevant profiles"
Bugs / Performance	crash, bug, glitch, slow, freeze, load, error	"App crashes every time I open chats"
Safety / Privacy	fake, bot, scam, privacy, data, report, block, verify	"Too many fake profiles and bots"

F-09 — Rating vs Sentiment Mismatch Detection
The system shall flag reviews where the star rating and sentiment polarity are inconsistent. A mismatch is defined as:
•Star rating 4–5 AND classified sentiment is Negative
•Star rating 1–2 AND classified sentiment is Positive
Flagged reviews shall be surfaced in the dashboard as a dedicated 'Anomalies' tab with the review text, star rating, and predicted sentiment displayed side by side.

F-10 — Fake / Spam Review Detection
The system shall identify potentially fake or bot-generated reviews using:
•Cosine similarity clustering: reviews with TF-IDF cosine similarity > 0.90 flagged as duplicates
•Length heuristics: reviews with < 3 words flagged as low-quality
•Repetition ratio: reviews where >50% of tokens are repeated flagged as spam
Detection results shall be output as a flagged_reviews.csv file and displayed in the dashboard.

5. Non-Functional Requirements

Category	Requirement
Performance	Full pipeline (5,000 reviews) must complete in under 5 minutes on a standard laptop (8GB RAM, modern CPU). Dashboard must load in < 2 seconds.
Accuracy	Sentiment classifier must achieve a minimum macro F1-score of 0.85 on the test set. Results must be reproducible.
Scalability	The pipeline must handle up to 50,000 reviews without code changes. Batch processing must be used for BERT inference.
Usability	Dashboard UI must be operable without any training. All charts must include axis labels and legends. Colour scheme must be accessible (WCAG AA contrast).
Maintainability	All modules must have docstrings. A requirements.txt and README with setup instructions must be included. Code must pass flake8 linting.
Portability	The project must run on Windows, macOS, and Linux using a standard Python virtual environment. Docker support is a bonus.



6. System Architecture

6.1 High-Level NLP Pipeline
The system follows a modular pipeline architecture with clearly defined stages:

Stage	Description	Input	Output
1. Collect	Scrape Google Play reviews via API	App package IDs	raw_reviews.csv
2. Preprocess	Clean, tokenise, lemmatise text	raw_reviews.csv	clean_reviews.csv
3. Extract	TF-IDF / BERT embeddings	clean_reviews.csv	feature_matrix
4. Classify	Sentiment model inference	feature_matrix	sentiment_labels.csv
5. Analyse	Aspect extraction, mismatch, trends	sentiment_labels.csv	analysis_results.json
6. Visualise	Dashboard rendering, word clouds, charts	analysis_results.json	Web Dashboard

