7. Dashboard Specification

The dashboard shall be built using React (Vite) on the frontend and FastAPI on the backend. It shall consist of the following views/tabs:

7.1 Overview Tab
•Total review count, date range, average star rating (KPI cards)
•Sentiment distribution donut chart (Positive / Negative)
•Overall sentiment score (composite index 0–100)
•Top 3 most mentioned words across all reviews

7.2 Trends Tab
•Monthly sentiment trend line chart (2 lines: Positive, Negative)
•Review volume bar chart over time
•Ability to overlay app update dates as vertical markers

7.3 Aspects Tab
•Grouped bar chart: sentiment breakdown per aspect (UI, Pricing, Matches, Bugs, Safety)
•Clickable aspect filter: shows representative reviews for that aspect
•Aspect sentiment heatmap for cross-app comparison

7.4 Word Cloud Tab
•Separate word clouds for Positive and Negative reviews
•Adjustable minimum frequency slider
•Downloadable as PNG

7.5 Anomalies Tab
•Table of rating-sentiment mismatch reviews
•Table of flagged fake/spam reviews
•Filter by app, date, or mismatch type

7.6 Compare Tab
•Side-by-side sentiment comparison: Tinder vs Bumble vs Hinge
•Radar chart for aspect-level comparison
•Narrative auto-summary generated by the NLG module

7.7 Upload Tab
•CSV file upload interface
•Column mapping wizard (map CSV columns to required fields)
•Real-time processing progress indicator
•Auto-redirect to Overview tab after processing



8. Data Requirements

8.1 Data Schema
Each review record shall conform to the following schema:
Field	Type	Description
review_id	String	Unique identifier for each review
app_name	String	Application name (tinder / bumble / hinge)
review_text	String	Raw review text as posted by the user
clean_text	String	Preprocessed review text
star_rating	Integer (1–5)	User-assigned star rating
review_date	Date (YYYY-MM-DD)	Date the review was posted
thumbs_up	Integer	Number of helpful votes received
sentiment_label	Enum (Pos/Neg)	Predicted sentiment classification
sentiment_score	Float (0.0–1.0)	Confidence score for predicted label
aspect_sentiments	JSON Object	Per-aspect sentiment labels and scores
is_mismatch	Boolean	Flag for rating vs sentiment inconsistency
is_spam	Boolean	Flag for detected fake or duplicate review

