12. Glossary

Term	Definition
Sentiment Analysis	NLP technique to identify the emotional tone of text as positive, negative, or neutral
ABSA	Aspect-Based Sentiment Analysis — identifying sentiment for specific product/service dimensions within a review
BERT	Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers — a pre-trained deep learning model for NLP tasks
VADER	Valence Aware Dictionary and sEntiment Reasoner — a rule-based sentiment analysis tool optimised for social media text
TF-IDF	Term Frequency–Inverse Document Frequency — a numerical statistic used as a text feature for machine learning
NLG	Natural Language Generation — automatically generating natural language text from structured data
MoSCoW	Prioritisation framework: Must Have, Should Have, Could Have, Won't Have
F1-Score	Harmonic mean of precision and recall; used to evaluate classification model performance


